What is it like for men to buy sanitary pads for women? Why is it taboo? And should men be embarrassed? 
#feminism #menstruation #period #periodproblems #women
@boatz_an_hoez ain't playin #period #skylark

I got my period yesterday and realised I was out of tampons and sanitary pads. 
We were hosting people over for an afternoon tea and I was in the middle of getting everything ready, so I asked my husband if he could go out and get me what I needed, before I bleed all over the kitchen floor.

When he got back he told me that the lady in the store was very impressed by him buying me tamponts and even said "you're a very good husband, most men wouldn't do that". Now I'm not sure about "most men", but I have no doubt that any guy who is "man enough" to walk around a store looking for the 'extra strong flow' pads his wife asked him for, use the discount cuppons that have been hanging on the fridge for a month AND not miss out on the 'buy two get one for free' deal - is a keeper! 
And as for the rest of you guys, news flash - we bleed. 
Deal with it ♡
